  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  (1) Health patients, American Society of Anesthesiologists (ASA) I or II

          -  (2) Patients who need to submit tooth extraction (pre-molar, canine and incisor teeth
             - uniradicular teeth or teeth with fused roots) which present ideal conditions to
             receive dental implants after 3 months.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Smoking

          -  Systemic diseases related with healing disorders

          -  Poor oral hygiene

          -  Pregnant or lactating patient

          -  Use of flap elevation for dental extraction
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
